items.title: Senecio glomeratus subsp. glomeratus
items.content_text: 3 plants together then no more seen elsewhere at this site. Not recorded previously here so I wouldn't be surprised if it were an occasional blow-in.

items.title: Gaudinia fragilis
items.content_text: Growing within a few feet of the lake.

items.title: Eleocharis pusilla
items.content_text: Tiny Eleocharis, at least half the size of E. acuta in all respects. Well hidden among other plants.

items.title: Epilobium billardierianum subsp. intermedium
items.content_text: Keys out quite well to intermedium although the few plants I saw wouldn't be described as freely branching. Two individuals pictured here.

items.title: Montia australasica
items.content_text: Fooled me for a while because the first plant had 6 petals (see 3rd pic).

items.title: Isolepis cernua var. platycarpa
items.content_text: This tiny plant has been recorded here previously. Glumes look a little acute so can't discount I. marginata.
